:Namespace world
    ‚éēIO ‚Üź 0
    'foldl' 'packR'‚éēCY'dfns'

    l ‚Üź 16 128 16
    box ‚Üź ‚äÉ‚ąė.‚ą®/1@0¬®l-‚ćõ‚ÜĎ¬®1

    view_distance ‚Üź 8
    max_chunks ‚Üź 2*‚ć®1+2√óview_distance

    ‚ćĚ The maximum possible surface can be visualized as a
    ‚ćĚ   3d checkerboard. We need to also account for the edges
    ‚ćĚ   of the chunk
    ‚ćĚ This is:
    ‚ćĚ  6√ó‚Ćą2√∑‚ć®√ó/¬Į2+l    - Inner
    ‚ćĚ  6√ó(√ó/-√ó/‚ć§-‚ąė2)l  - Outer
    max_faces ‚Üź 6√ó‚Ćą2√∑‚ć®√ó/¬Į2+l
    max_faces +‚Üź 6√ó(√ó/-√ó/‚ć§-‚ąė2) l

    ‚ćĚ For each face we need 4 vertices and 6 indices
    ‚ćĚ Furthermore, we need the amount of info per vertex and size of indices
    (vsize isize) ‚Üź (4√ó4√ómax_faces ‚čĄ 4√ó6√ómax_faces)

    vb_sizes ‚Üź ‚Ćą0 0.35 0.7 1.0 √ó vsize
    vb_pools ‚Üź ‚ć¨ ‚ć¨ ‚ć¨
    vb_start_lens ‚Üź ‚Ćä1.0 0.1 0.1√ómax_chunks

    ‚ćĚ vbs that aren't done being used by the gpu
    ‚ćĚ (fence counter, index into vb_pools, vb pointer)
    ‚ćĚ freed vbs are added with fence pointer 0 and when fence is
    ‚ćĚ   retrieved, they're set with func Push_fence.
    ‚ćĚ Released with Pop_fence
    vb_fenced ‚Üź 0 3‚ćī0

    ib ‚Üź 0
    tb ‚Üź 0
    tb_pos ‚Üź 0
    tb_size ‚Üź ‚Ćä2√óvsize
    ‚ćĚ Vector of x and z positions corresponding to xz column
    tb_queue ‚Üź ‚ć¨
    (texture sampler) ‚Üź ‚ć¨ ‚ć¨

    chunks ‚Üź 0‚ćī‚ć®0,l
